.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hsh - simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input and executes them.

It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH USAGE
.SS Interactive mode
Run the shell and type commands:

.nf
$ ./hsh
($) ls
($) exit
.fi

.SS Non-interactive mode
Pipe commands into the shell:

.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
.fi

.SH FEATURES
.IP (bu 2
Executes standard UNIX commands
.IP (bu 2
Supports environment variable display
.IP (bu 2
Handles basic process execution

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command.

